<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFE4393CEBD2C108FE6F5DFF" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE4393CEBD2C108FEA35D63" blockId="74.[227,348,1595,1621]" box="[227,348,1595,1621]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<heading id="5A24A609FFE4393CEBD2C108FEA35D63" bold="true" box="[227,348,1595,1621]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE4393CEBD2C108FEA35D63" bold="true" box="[227,348,1595,1621]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE4393CEBD2C159FE6F5DFF" blockId="74.[227,1436,1641,1737]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">OL/OH = 1.71–1.94, OsL/CaL = 0.77–1.00. Elongate otoliths with large rostrum and blunt posterior rim. Oval ostium with oblong colliculum. Elongate and narrow cauda of over ½ OL, with crest-like crista superior.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="49C942EEFFE4393CEBD2C1C3FE175C6D" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE4393CEBD2C1C3FE955C3C" blockId="74.[227,362,1776,1802]" box="[227,362,1776,1802]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<heading id="5A24A609FFE4393CEBD2C1C3FE955C3C" bold="true" box="[227,362,1776,1802]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FFE4393CEBD2C1C3FE955C3C" bold="true" box="[227,362,1776,1802]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFE4393CEBD2C02EFE175C6D" blockId="74.[227,1436,1821,1883]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">This species is dedicated to Thomas Yancey for his much appreciated support during our field work in the Brazos River area.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
